In the chaos that followed a massive concentrated ground, a battle was fought between the two sides, with both sides deploying huge amounts of artillery and aircraft to support their respective nations on the ground. However, utilizing the technological advancements and development made by the Catgirls and the Capuchins, the Catgirls utilize orbital bombardment installations around Mars and large laser cannons built on Titans to absolutely damage logistical facilities utilized by the Martians, causing for them to be unable to fight the battle in the long-term.

Blood and steel are spilled. Hundreds of thousands dead. But the Ra'ki and Nal'xiso forces begin to withdraw. The Catgirls had successfully fended off enemy forces. The other Martian factions stop supporting the other two and decide to not engage with plans to invade the Catgirls.

Peace is signed with the Ra'ki and Nal'xiso with their colonies in the Asteroid Belt being divided up by the Capuchins and Catgirls.

Now the CCA alliance can focus its efforts on the Earth Coalition which is now slowly dividing itself due to turmoils on Earth. The loss of Hawaii from a clique of FBI agents couping it has caused for some Catgirl expeditionary units on Earth to evacuate some Hawaiian civils to safe facilities within the Asteroid Belt.

Elder of Defense for St Abbaddon.
Though my nation is called "Stratocratic-Anarchy Oceanic Empire", it's not actually 'anarchist' nor 'stratocratic'; not even an "empire". Oceania is a federal union of several constituent states with a president, a large legislature, and a democratic constitution. However, the nation was once the center of ideological strife between ideological factions. Hence this is why the Oceanic Mainland (the main landmass of Oceania) is split into two regions: "Anarchia" which consists of the eastern half of the Oceanic mainland. "Stratocratia" is the western half of the Oceanic Mainland.

(My nation name was actually typed in by accident. But I've kept it my nation name ever since)
